<HEADLINE>
FT  16 FEB 94 / 300 march to back striking lecturers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
About 300 people marched in support of striking lecturers at City of Bath
College yesterday in a dispute over new working conditions.
Nearly 50 academic staff, who have refused to sign new contracts, started a
two-day strike on Monday. The dispute has the backing of Natfhe, the
lecturers' union. More strikes are planned for Friday and next Monday and
Tuesday.
The strike action is a sharp escalation of the contracts row between Natfhe
and college principals. The college has tried to introduce new contracts
since colleges were removed from local authority control last April.
