FT  16 FEB 94 / Cuba to compensate Spaniards
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Nearly 1,500 Spaniards will be compensated for property that was
expropriated by Cuba following its 1959 revolution, the Spanish economy
ministry said yesterday, Reuter reports from Madrid.
The Spanish government will pay out Pta5.3bn (Pounds 25.7m) in indemnity
