<HEADLINE>
FT  15 FEB 94 / FT Guide to the Winter Olympics (3): Message from the
sponsors - Seiko
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Challenge is the essence of sport. Each and every Olympic Games comes alive
when the world sees young men and women who have the courage to put on
display their skill, their passion for excellence and their will to win. For
these athletes, the next 16 days in Lillehammer will be the ultimate
challenge of their sporting lives.
Seiko represents this spirit of challenge and will do justice to it by
providing to the athletes and their events the highest level of timing
technology ever seen at a winter sports event. Since 1964 when our
appointment as Official Timer to the Summer Olympic Games was the catalyst
for Seiko to develop Quartz Timing Technology, we have continuously set new
standards and accepted the challenge posed by the ever-increasing needs of
sport for timing systems accurate to the millisecond and capable of
instantaneous transmission to spectators, athletes and TV viewers
world-wide.
To our technology partners in the Olympic Family; to the Organiser of the
Games; and, most of all, to the athletes; we offer our commitment to help
Lillehammer 1994 be the best Winter Games in history.
Mr Masahiro Sekimoto President, Seiko Corporation
