FT  15 FEB 94 / FT Guide to the Winter Olympics (2): Message from the
sponsors - Kodak
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Kodak has been associated with the Olympics for many years, both as a
sponsor and provider of imaging products and services.
At Lillehammer, our ID system will help strengthen the security set up to
safeguard the athletes and spectators at the Games. We will speed diagnosis
and treatment of injuries by enabling the digital transmission of
radiographic images. Our cameras will supply images which can be downloaded
to a computer for viewing, editing and transmission - and our Photo CD
system will store and manage picture files.
Information is the breath of modern life. The way we communicate that
information will either help or hinder the way we understand and assimilate
it. This supplement has been designed to enhance our knowledge of the Winter
Games and the ideals of the Olympic movement. We are delighted to be a part
of it.
Mr Anthony J. WaterlowChairman and Managing Director, Kodak Limited
