FT  15 FEB 94 / Observer: Forming up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Place your bets, please, on who gets to run the UK National Lottery. William
Hill, the bookmaker, has opened a book on the sweepstake to beat all
sweepstakes. The 7-2 favourite is The Lottery Foundation, headed by Richard
Branson and Lord Young. Second favourite is The Great British Lottery
Company at 4-1. Games for Good Causes, in which William Hill's rival
Ladbroke has a stake, is trailing at 6-1. Last of the eight bidders is
Rainbow, at 20-1.
The smart money seems to be on Branson's bid. Indeed, Observer hears that
Will Whitehorn, the entrepreneur's mouthpiece, has bet Pounds 1000 of his
own money on Branson winning.
Sensibly, he never risked a penny betting on the chances of his master
winning an ITV franchise.
